000076C0                           827      
000076C0                           828  *------------------------------------------------------------------------------
000076C0                           829  * All exception handlers jump here to output the PC of the next instruction
000076C0                           830  * after the exception occured.
000076C0                           831  * A0 holds the address of a null terminated message to be displayed first.
000076C0                           832  *------------------------------------------------------------------------------
000076C0                           833  handleCleanUp:
000076C0  6100 0EC0                834      bsr.w   putString           * print out the relevant message
000076C4  202F 0002                835      move.l  2(a7),d0            * get the saved PC address
000076C8  6100 0E74                836      bsr.w   writeAddr32         * and display it
000076CC  6100 0EB0                837      bsr.w   putCRLF
000076D0                           838  .infloop:
000076D0  60FE                     839      bra.s   .infloop            * and stay here forever ...
